  "title": "Executive, Training & Capability Development",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>🔹 What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul><li>Support the design and delivery of training programmes and certifications</li><li>Coordinate with trainers, partners, and industry stakeholders</li><li>Manage programme logistics, communications, and reporting</li><li>Assist in outreach and partnerships that drive talent development</li></ul><p><strong>🔹 What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li>Degree/Diploma in Business, HR, Education or related fields</li><li>Fresh graduates or 1–2 years’ experience (MICE experience is a bonus!)</li><li>Strong organisational and communication skills</li><li>Familiarity with SkillsFuture and workforce development frameworks is a plus</li></ul><p><strong>🔹 Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li>Shape the future of Singapore’s MICE & Events workforce</li><li>Work on meaningful, impactful capability‑building initiatives</li><li>Collaborative and innovative team culture</li></ul>",
